liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Warren Mundine has begun his speech to the National Press Club. "Next month's Referendum is one of the most important in Australia's history," he says. "Australians will have a choice about what kind of nation we want to be: Do we want Australia to be a liberal democracy where all people are equal, where all Australians can be reconciled and moving ahead with a united purpose? Or do we want to be a country where people are divided by race and permanently in conflict with each other over facts of history that cannot be altered?"
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: Warren Mundine says the referendum is about what Australia wants the country to be

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Putting my hi-vis on for a moment... and further to Dave's earlier post about Gina Rinehart increasing her stake in lithium miner Liontown to more than 10 per cent, its shares have taken a hit this morning. The company is among the bottom 10 performers on the ASX 200 so far, having fallen 2.67 per cent to $2.92 a share. Today's trading session is also the first time shareholders have been able to react to Ms Rinehart's near $200 million shopping spree. So, perhaps not all of them are happy with having her as a bigger shareholder! This is going to be one to watch over the coming weeks.
